Here’s a concise outline with the latest items for Maria’s community update. Feel free to copy/paste or adjust as needed.

Case Updates (past month):
• Adjustment-of-status petition for one community member (initials C.R.) has been accepted by USCIS; interview expected late April/early May.
• Three DACA renewals were approved; work authorization cards already issued.
• An asylum application for a family of four advanced to a merits hearing now set for mid-May.
(Please keep individual names confidential when sharing publicly.)

Workshops & Clinics:
• Free Legal Advice Clinic – Sat, Feb 26, 10:00 AM-2:00 PM, Downtown Community Center, 123 Main St.
• Immigrant Rights & Resources Workshops – Tue Mar 1, Thu Mar 3, Sat Mar 5, 10:00 AM-12:00 PM each day, Community Resource Center, 1234 Elm St.

Additional Resources / Notices:
• New online FAQ covering recent public-charge rule changes: https://bit.ly/publicchargeFAQ
• USCIS fee-increase proposal is open for public comment until Mar 13; encourage community members to submit feedback here: https://www.federalregister.gov/documents/fee-proposal

Let me know if you need any tweaks.

Best,
John","cc":null,"bcc":null,"execution_log_path":"data/logs/item61_execution_log.json","card_path":"data/agent_cards/item61_recipient.json"}
